Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the analysis of bit-interleaved coded modulation (BICM) using a mismatched decoding model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses communication systems and coding techniques, which suggests the sub-categories cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions symbol decoding metrics and iterative decoding, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
